   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Providing Clean Water For Rural Communities</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Contaminated water and poor sanitation are linked to transmission of diseases such as cholera, diarrhea, dysentery, hepatitis A, typhoid, and polio. Absent, inadequate, or inappropriately managed water and sanitation services expose individuals to preventable health risks. Also, Better water sources is one of the most important substances on earth. It is in this perspective that Superlily Foundation is swinging into action to give clean water to rural communities.</narrative>
  </description>
